ONMEBOL)|2010 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 2. || 18 June 2009 || [[Loftus Versfeld Stadium]], [[Pretoria]], South Africa || {{fb|USA}} || <center>'''1'''\u20130</center> ||  <center>3\u20130</center> || [[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n;Flamengo\n*[[Campeonato Carioca]]: 2001\n*[[Copa dos Campe\u00f5es]]: 2001\n\n;Cruzeiro\n*[[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A]]: [[2003 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|2003]]\n\n;Galatasaray\n*[[S\u00fcper Lig]]: [[2011\u201312 S\u00fcer Lig|2011\u201312]], [[2012\u201313 S\u00fcper Lig|2012\u201313]], [[2014\u201315 S\u00fcper Lig|2014\u201315]]\n*[[Turkish Cup]]: [[2013\u201314 Turkish Cup|2013\u201314]], [[2014\u201315 Turkish Cup|2014\u201315]]\n*[[Turkish Super Cup]]: [[2012 Turkish Super Cup|2012]], [[2013 Turkish Super Cup|2013]], [[2015 Turkish Super Cup|2015]]\n\n;Palmeiras\n*[[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A]]: [[2018 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|2018]]\n\n===International===\n;Brazil\n*[[FIFA Confederations Cup]] : [[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup|2009]]\n\n===Individual===\n*Sambafoot Brazilian Player of the Year: 2012, 2013 (Fourth Place)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.galatasaray.org/futbol/haber/15587.php|title=GALATASARAY.ORG|publisher=}}</ref>\n*[[Campeonato Paulista]] Team of the year: [[2017 Campeonato Paulista|2017]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/sp/futebol/campeonato-paulista/noticia/com-cinco-jogadores-e-carille-campeao-corinthians-e-base-da-selecao-do-paulistao.ghtml|title=Com cinco jogadores e Carille, campe\u00e3o Corinthians \u00e9 base da sele\u00e7\u00e3o do Paulist\u00e3o|trans-title=With five players and Carille, champion Corinthians is the baseline of the ''Paulist\u00e3o'' team of the year|work=Globo Esporte|language=pt|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=21 May 2017}}</ref> [[2018 Campeonato Paulista|2018]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://futebolpaulista.com.br/Noticias/Detalhe.aspx?Noticia=7158|title=Com dom\u00ednio do Palmeiras, Sele\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e9 premiada recheada de finalistas|trans-title=With prevalence of Palmeiras, Best XI is awarded full of finalists|publisher=[[Federa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Futebol]]|language=pt|date=9 April 2018|access-date=10 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{NFT player|id=29935}}\n* {{UEFA player|250002677}}\n* {{FIFA player|194818|Felipe Melo}}\n* [http://www.habermonitor.com/en/haber/trend/felipe-melo News about the Felipe Melo] (Turkish Version)\n* {{TFF player|1432017}}\n* [http://www.galatasaray.org/futboltakimi/pages/oyuncu_892.php Profile] at Galatasaray.org\n* {{ESPN FC|48735}}\n* {{Sambafoot|884_Felipe_Melo}}\n* {{soccerway|felipe-melo-de-carvalho/3288}}\n\n{{Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Brazil squad\n| bg    = #FBEC5D\n| fg    = #008000\n| list1 = \n{{Brazil squad 2009 FIFA Confederations Cup}}\n{{Brazil squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Melo, Felipe}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Volta Redonda]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A players]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:S\u00fcper Lig players]]\n[[Category:Clube de Regatas do Flamengo footballers]]\n[[Category:Cruzeiro Esporte Clube players]]\n[[Category:Gr\u00eamio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense players]]\n[[Category:Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras players]]\n[[Category:Racing de Santander players]]\n[[Category:RCD Mallorca players]]\n[[Category:UD Almer\u00eda players]]\n[[Category:ACF Fiorentina players]]\n[[Category:Juventus F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Galatasaray S.K. footballers]]\n[[Category:Inter Milan players]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Brazil international footballers]]\n[[Category:2009 FIFA Confederations Cup players]]\n[[Category:FIFA Confederations Cup-winning players]]\n[[Category:Brazilian Christians]]\n[[Category:2010 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Outfield association footballers who played in goal]]\n", "text_old": "{{For2|the writer|[[Filipe Melo]]|the Portuguese footballer|[[Filipe Melo (footballer)]]}}\n{{Short description|Brazilian association football player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Portuguese name|Melo|Carvalho}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Felipe Melo\n| image          = Felipe Melo 2014-15.JPG\n| image_size  = 200\n| caption        =  Melo playing for [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] in 2014.\n| fullname       = Felipe Melo de Carvalho<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.inter.it/en/news/54383/inter-submit-squad-for-uel-group-stages |title=Inter submit squad for UEL group stages |publisher=Inter Milan |date=1 September 2016 |accessdate=21 May 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1983|6|26}}\n| birth_place    = [[Volta Redonda]], Brazil\n| height         = {{convert|1.83|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position       = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub    = [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]]\n| clubnumber     = 30\n| youthyears1    =\n| youthclubs1    =\n| years1 = 2001\u20132003\n| clubs1 = [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]]\n| caps1 = 24 \n| goals1 = 3\n| years2 = 2003\n| clubs2 = [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]]\n| caps2 = 31 \n| goals2 = 2\n| years3 = 2004\n| clubs3 = [[Gr\u00eamio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|Gr\u00eamio]]\n| caps3 = 19 \n| goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2005\n| clubs4 = [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]]\n| caps4 = 8  \n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2005\u20132007\n| clubs5 = [[Racing de Santander|Racing Santander]]\n| caps5 = 49 \n| goals5 = 6\n| years6 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs6 = [[UD Almer\u00eda|Almer\u00eda]]\n| caps6 = 39 \n| goals6 = 7\n| years7 = 2008\u20132009\n| clubs7 = [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]\n| caps7 = 29 \n| goals7 = 2\n| years8 = 2009\u20132011\n| clubs8 = [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]\n| caps8 = 58 \n| goals8 = 4\n| years9 = 2011\u20132015\n| clubs9 =  [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]]\n| caps9 = 114\n| goals9 = 15\n| years10 = 2015\u20132017\n| clubs10 = [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]]\n| caps10 = 31\n| goals10 = 1\n| years11= 2017\u2013\n| clubs11 = [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]]\n| caps11  = 42\n| goals11 = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\u20132010 \n| nationalteam1  = [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 22\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| medaltemplates =\n{{MedalCountry|{{flagu|Brazil}}}}\n{{MedalSport|[[Association football|Football]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[FIFA Confederations Cup]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup|2009 Confederations Cup]]|}}\n| pcupdate       = 20 December 2018\n| ntupdate       = \n}}\n\n'''Felipe Melo de Carvalho''' (born 26 June 1983) is a Brazilian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for  [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]].\n\nHe began his career with [[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A]] teams [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]], [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]] and [[Gr\u00eamio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|Gr\u00eamio]], before moving to Spain in 2005, where he represented [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]], [[Racing de Santander|Racing Santander]] and [[UD Almer\u00eda|Almer\u00eda]] in [[La Liga]]. After one year at [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]], he signed for [[Juventus]] for \u20ac25&nbsp;million in 2009. Melo spent four seasons at [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]], playing 154 total games and winning eight honours including three [[S\u00fcper Lig]] titles. After a spell back in [[Serie A]] with [[Inter Milan]], he returned to Brazil in 2017 by signing for [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], where he soon won the [[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A]] in 2018.\n                                                                                  \nMelo was a [[Brazil national football team|Brazilian international]] from 2009 to 2010, earning 22 caps and scoring two goals. He was part of their squads that won the [[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup]] and reached the quarter-finals of the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Brazil===\nMelo began his career for [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]], where he made 69 appearances and scored no goals in his two-season spell with the club. Following impressive performances with Flamengo, Melo transferred to [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]] in the summer of 2003, but would remain for just one season. In his single season with Cruzeiro, Melo managed to make 31 league appearances, scoring two goals. Following yet another impressive season in Brazil, he was sold to [[Gr\u00eamio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|Gr\u00eamio]].\n\nFollowing his transfer to Gr\u00eamio, Melo managed to make an additional 19 appearances and adding three goals to his tally in his native Brazil. He would only remain in [[Porto Alegre]] for 2004, because Gr\u00eamio was relegated that year and the team was dismantled.\n\n===Spain===\nIn January 2005, Melo moved abroad for the first time, joining Spanish [[La Liga]] club [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]], who released [[Andrija Deliba\u0161i\u0107]] to give him a place.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mallorca apresenta Felipe Melo e libera s\u00e9rvio|trans-title=Mallorca present Felipe Melo and release Serbian |url=http://esportes.terra.com.br/futebol/europeu/interna/0,,OI461993-EI2030,00-Mallorca+apresenta+Felipe+Melo+e+libera+servio.html |accessdate=13 August 2018 |agency=EFE |publisher=Terra |date=27 January 2005 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He played only eight times for the [[Balearic Islands|Balearic]] team, his season ending through knee ligament injury against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in March;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Acedo |first1=Francisco |title=Melo blow for Mallorca |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11845/2333110/melo-blow-for-mallorca |accessdate=13 August 2018 |publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> they narrowly avoided relegation.\n\nAhead of the 2005\u201306 season, Melo moved to fellow league team [[Racing de Santander]]. He scored his first goal for them on 21 December, in a 2\u20131 win away to [[Real Madrid]] at the [[Santiago Bernab\u00e9u Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Llamas |first1=Fernando |title=El Racing tambi\u00e9n supera al Madrid para cerrar el a\u00f1o |trans-title=Racing also overcome Madrid to close the year|url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundodeporte/2005/12/21/futbol/1135179014.html |accessdate=13 August 2018 |work=El Mundo |date=22 December 2005 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 July 2007, Melo became [[UD Almer\u00eda|Almer\u00eda]]'s first signing ahead of their debut top-flight season. The transfer, which involved buying some of his rights from a [[Third-party ownership in association football|third-party owner]], was the most expensive in the club's history.<ref>{{cite news |title=Felipe Melo, primer refuerzo del Almer\u00eda en Primera|trans-title=Felipe Melo, Almer\u00eda's first signing in ''Primera'' |url=http://www.diariocordoba.com/noticias/deportes/felipe-melo-primer-refuerzo-almeria-primera_334328.html |accessdate=13 August 2018 |work=Diario de C\u00f3rdoba |agency=EFE |date=3 July 2007 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He was a regular in midfield for [[Unai Emery]]'s team, contributing seven goals as the [[Andalusia]]ns finished 8th.\n\n===Fiorentina===\nAfter a successful first season at Almer\u00eda, Melo agreed to transfer to Italian side Fiorentina in a reported \u20ac13&nbsp;million transfer for the [[2008\u201309 ACF Fiorentina season|2008\u201309 season]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.as.com/futbol/articulo/felipe-melo-ficha-fiorentina/20080313dasdasftb_19/Tes|title=Felipe Melo ficha por la Fiorentina|date=13 March 2008|accessdate=26 December 2010|work=AS|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.udalmeriasad.com/udalmeria/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=1305&Itemid=77\n |title       = F\u00fatbol sala para terminar\n |access-date  = 2 July 2009\n |work        = [[UD Almer\u00eda|Almer\u00eda]]\n |url-status     = dead\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20090725024932/http://www.udalmeriasad.com/udalmeria/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=1305&Itemid=77\n |archive-date = 25 July 2009\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> Having held Spanish nationality since the 2007\u201308 season, he was not counted as a non-EU player in the Italian Serie A.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/it/news/7/calciomercato/2009/07/23/1398537/felipe-melo-prego-e-picchio|title=Felipe Melo: \"Prego e picchio\"|date=23 July 2009|accessdate=5 December 2010|agency=TuttoSport|work= Goal.com|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nHe made his debut in the first leg of the third qualifying round of the [[UEFA Champions League]] against [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]], and scored his first goal in a ''Viola'' shirt against [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] in the Serie A. After a very impressive debut season in the Serie A, which included 29 appearances and two goals, the Brazilian transferred to [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] in [[Turin]].\n\n===Juventus===\nOn 30 June 2009, following a lauded performance at the [[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup]], Melo signed a new five-year contract with Fiorentina,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://it.violachannel.tv/dettaglio-ultimora/items/melo-dino-al-2013.html|title=Comunicato Stampa|date=30 June 2009|accessdate=19 July 2009|publisher=ACF Fiorentina|language=Italian}}</ref> with a release clause of \u20ac25&nbsp;million. At this point, [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] was reportedly in negotiations to sign the player.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://it.violachannel.tv/dettaglio-ultimora/items/comunicato-stampa.2220.html|title=Comunicato Stampa|date=4 July 2009|accessdate=19 July 2009|publisher=ACF Fiorentina|language=Italian}}</ref> Within days, however, Melo was the subject of a bid from Juventus. The two [[ACF Fiorentina\u2013Juventus F.C. rivalry|rival clubs]] eventually agreed a fee of \u20ac25&nbsp;million in total and Juve's [[Marco Marchionni]] joined Fiorentina on 15 July 2009 for a tagged price of \u20ac4.5 million.<ref name=uefamelo>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=846751.html|title=Juventus snare Felipe Melo|publisher=UEFA|date= 16 July 2009|accessdate=7 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n| url        = http://www.juventus.com/site/eng/NEWS_newseventi_D231870518C04C52AEA44D74FE8CA28D.asp| title= Official: Felipe Melo joins Juventus| accessdate = 14 July 2009| work= [[Juventus F.C.]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/site/filesite/finance/comunicatipricesensitive/comunicato_15072009_melo_e_marchionni_eng.pdf |title=Milano, 20 giugno 2004 |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=15 June 2010}}</ref> Later, [[Cristiano Zanetti]], tagged for \u20ac2&nbsp;million, re-joined Fiorentina.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.juventus.com/site/filesite/finance/comunicatipricesensitive/comunicato_10082009_zanetti_eng.pdf|title=Agreement with ACF Fiorentina S.p.A. for the disposal of the player C. Zanetti|date=10 August 2009|accessdate=10 August 2009|publisher=Juventus}}</ref> This allowed Juve to pay Fiorentina \u20ac18.5 million in three instalments.\n\nThe first half of the [[2009\u201310 Serie A|2009\u201310 season]] was one to forget despite a bright start to his Juve career. He scored his first Juve goal against top-of-the-table rivals [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] in a 3\u20131 win. In the December [[Derby d'Italia]] fixture at home, he was controversially sent off for a supposed elbow at [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]]'s [[Mario Balotelli]]. The incident sparked a fiery argument between his teammate [[Gianluigi Buffon]] and Inter midfielder [[Thiago Motta]], and both had to be separated by Inter and Juve players. Melo was instrumental in his sides win over [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] at the [[San Siro]] in [[2010\u201311 Serie A|2010\u201311 season]], and was later voted man of the match.\n\n===Galatasaray===\nOn 22 July 2011, Melo joined [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] in Turkey on a season-long loan deal for \u20ac1.5 million, with an option to transfer permanently at the end of the season for \u20ac13 million.<ref>[http://www.galatasaray.org/futbol/futbol_as/haber/10675.php Felipe Melo Galatasaray\u2019da {{in lang|tr}}&#125;]. Galatasaray.org. Retrieved on 31 May 2012.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.juventus.com/wps/wcm/connect/285825ce-37b4-43d3-9b90-59c1d92b9b08/comunicato+22072011+melo+eng.pdf?MOD=AJPERES&CACHEID=285825ce-37b4-43d3-9b90-59c1d92b9b08|title=Agreement with Galatasaray for the disposal of the player Felipe Melo|date=22 July 2011|access-date=29 July 2011|work=Juventus F.C.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150606143243/http://www.juventus.com/wps/wcm/connect/285825ce-37b4-43d3-9b90-59c1d92b9b08/comunicato+22072011+melo+eng.pdf?MOD=AJPERES&CACHEID=285825ce-37b4-43d3-9b90-59c1d92b9b08|archive-date=6 June 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> He agreed on a contract with a net annual salary of \u20ac3.3 million plus a per-appearance bonus of \u20ac30,000,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kap.gov.tr/yay/Bildirim/Bildirim.aspx?id=162152|title=Felipe Melo de Carvalho'nun Juventus Football Club SPA'dan sat\u0131n alma opsiyonlu olarak kiralanmas\u0131 hakk\u0131nda|trans-title=Felipe Melo de Carval from Juventus Football Club SPA on loan with option to purchase|date=22 July 2011|accessdate=28 July 2011|work=Galatasaray|publisher=Turkish Public Disclosure System|language=Turkish}}</ref> replacing departed [[Lorik Cana]] as the club's new central midfielder. He was attributed to the nickname \"Pitbull\" by the team supporters because of his passionate playing style, which also helped him become a fans favourite quickly; it is said that he displayed the mutual respect back with his tattoo of the club's mascot, a lion, on his arm.<ref name=\"Turkish-football.com\">[http://www.turkish-football.com/news_read.php?id=2111 Felipe Melo tattoo (speculation)] turkish-football.com (English) accessed 29 May 2010</ref> This is not true, however, because in his own statement, he states that this is a coincidence and that he got the tattoo due to the fact that in Brazil, a lion is a symbol for Jesus Christ.<ref name=\"habermonitor.com\">[http://www.habermonitor.com/en/haber/detay/saved-by-3-points-melo-galatasaray/14681/ Saved by 3 points Melo Galatasaray (Statement)] habermonitor.com (Turkish w/ English option)</ref>\n\nMelo scored his first goal on 18 September 2011 from a 35-metre-long shot against [[Samsunspor]]. He scored 12 goals in 36 league matches, and at the end of the season, he was among the champion squad.\n\nMelo had been expected to make a permanent move to Galatasaray, but on 24 July, transfer fee negotiations between the club and Juventus broke down due to the Turkish club requesting a lower fee for the player.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story/_/id/1126608/juventus'-felipe-melo-galatasaray-talks-break-down?cc=5739|title=Juventus' Felipe Melo Galatasaray talks break down|publisher=ESPN FC}}</ref>  On 14 August, the two clubs were able to agree another loan deal sending Melo to Turkey for the [[2012\u201313 S\u00fcper Lig|2012\u201313 season]], for \u20ac1.75 million, with the agreement including \"the option, to be exercised by Galatasaray by 30 April 2013, for the permanent acquisition of the player for a price of \u20ac6.5 million\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story/_/id/1133850/juventus'-felipe-melo-rejoins-galatasaray-on-loan-?cc=5901|title=Melo rejoins Galatasaray on loan |work=ESPNSoccernet |date=14 August 2012}}</ref> Melo also had a wage cut to \u20ac2.9 million with an appearances-based bonus of \u20ac25,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kap.gov.tr/yay/Bildirim/Bildirim.aspx?id=229529|title=KAP|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 November, in a game between Galatasaray and [[Sanica Boru Elaz\u0131\u011fspor|Elaz\u0131\u011fspor]] in the [[S\u00fcper Lig]], Melo saved a penalty after regular goalkeeper [[Fernando Muslera]] had committed a foul and been sent off and Galatasaray had already used all their substitutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2012/11/24/felipe-melo-vira-goleiro-pega-penalti-no-ultimo-minuto-e-salva-galatasaray-na-turquia.htm|title=Felipe Melo vira goleiro, pega p\u00eanalti no \u00faltimo minuto e salva Galatasaray na Turquia|work=UOL Esporte}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 July 2013, Melo made a permanent move to Galatasaray on a three-year contract worth \u20ac3.1 million plus bonuses, while the transfer fee was reduced to \u20ac3.75 million plus bonuses of a maximum \u20ac500,000, which the club activated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/media/native/investor-relations-docs/italiano/bilanci/1314/Relazione+finanziaria+annuale+30_06_2014.pdf |title=Relazione finanziaria annuale al 30 giugno 2014 |date=2 October 2014 |access-date=7 August 2015 |publisher=Juventus F.C. |language=Italian |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001001720/http://www.juventus.com/media/native/investor-relations-docs/italiano/bilanci/1314/Relazione+finanziaria+annuale+30_06_2014.pdf |archive-date=1 October 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=Gala>{{cite news| title =Felipe Melo joins Galatasaray  | url =http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/12691/8832642/galatasaray-sign-brazilian-midfielder-felipe-melo-from-juventus | publisher=Sky Sports | date=20 July 2013 |accessdate =July 2013|language=tr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kap.gov.tr/en/search/notice-results.aspx?id=299156|title=KAP|publisher=}}</ref> He made his 100th appearance for the club on 2 February 2014 in S\u00fcper Lig encounter against [[Bursaspor]] in a 6\u20130 home win.<ref name=Eurosport1>{{cite news| title =Felipe Melo Galatasaray formas\u0131yla 100. ma\u00e7\u0131na \u00e7\u0131kacak  | url =http://tr.eurosport.com/futbol/super-lig/2013-2014/felipe-melo-galatasaray-formasiyla-100.-macina-cikacak_sto4119050/story.shtml | work=[[Eurosport|Eurosport Turkish Edition]] | date=2 February 2014 |accessdate =2 February 2014|language=tr}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 August 2015, Melo signed a four-year contract extension; during the first season of said contract, the yearly salary remained unchanged at \u20ac3.1 million, but is set to be reduced to \u20ac2.6 million for next three seasons.<ref>https://www.kap.org.tr/tr/Bildirim/460875</ref> As of 2015, he is the most decorated Brazilian player in Turkish domestic competitions, winning seven cups, beating the record of his fellow countryman and ex-Galatasaray [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] [[Cl\u00e1udio Taffarel]].<ref name=2015TurkishCup>{{cite news|title=Melo ma\u00e7 sonunda \u015foke etti!|url=http://amkspor.sozcu.com.tr/2015/06/04/melo-mac-sonunda-soke-etti-422204/|work=[[S\u00f6zc\u00fc|AMK]]|language=Turkish|date=3 June 2015|accessdate=4 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Internazionale===\nOn 31 August 2015, Melo returned to Italy to sign with Internazionale<ref>http://www.inter.it/en/news/48883/felipe-melo-joins-inter</ref> on a 2-year contract and a \u20ac3.7 million transfer fee, plus \u20ac500,000 bonuses for each [[UEFA Champions League]] group stage qualification of the club, up to the 2017\u201318 season. Melo also received  \u20ac657,500 from Galatasaray.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kap.gov.tr/en/search/notice-results.aspx?id=464916|title=Felipe Melo De Carvalho \u2013 Transfer|date=1 September 2015|access-date=5 November 2015|author=Galatasaray |publisher=Turkish Public Disclosure System (KAP)|language=Turkish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/72388/official-felipe-melo-inter|title=Official: Felipe Melo to Inter \u2013 Football Italia|publisher=}}</ref> He officially returned to Serie A play on 23 September 2015 against [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]], against which he also scored his first goal for Inter.\n\n=== Palmeiras ===\nOn 8 January 2017, [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras]] announced the signing of Melo on a 3-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.palmeiras.com.br/noticias/id/38877|title=Multicampe\u00e3o, Felipe Melo assina com o Palmeiras at\u00e9 o fim de 2019|date=8 January 2017|access-date=12 January 2017|publisher=Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|language=Portuguese}}</ref> Four days later Inter announced that it was a loan until 30 June,<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.inter.it/it/news/78141/felipe-melo-al-palmeiras|title=Felipe Melo al Palmeiras|trans-title=Felipe Melo to Palmeiras|date=12 January 2017|access-date=6 September 2017|publisher=F.C. Internazionale Milano|language=Italian}}</ref> with his contract with Inter was set to expire on the same day.\n\n==International career==\nMelo made his international debut for [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] on 10 February 2009 against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in a friendly match, which Brazil won 2\u20130. He scored his first goal in the [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2010 FIFA World Cup qualification]] over [[Peru national football team|Peru]]. Brazil won 3\u20130. At the [[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup]], Melo scored the opening goal in a 3\u20130 victory over the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], in the group stage. Melo started all five games at the competition as Brazil went on to win the trophy.\n\nMelo was named in Brazil's final 23-man squad for the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]]. In Brazil's [[2010 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|quarter final]] against the Netherlands in [[Port Elizabeth]], Felipe Melo provided the assist for [[Robinho]]'s tenth-minute opener, before Melo himself slightly touched a [[Wesley Sneijder]] cross, which at first was recorded as an own goal, but later credited to Sneijder. Sneijder then put the Dutch 2\u20131 ahead, before Melo was then sent off by referee [[Yuichi Nishimura]] in the 73rd minute for a violent stamp on Dutch winger [[Arjen Robben]].<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?click_id=2822&art_id=nw20100702174021456C685909&set_id= | title = Brazil's Felipe Melo sent off for stamping | accessdate =2 July 2010 }}</ref> On Brazil's return home after the World Cup, Melo took the brunt of the criticism of the fans as they threw insults, pushed and shoved towards the players.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/world-cup/story/_/id/805973/ce/uk/?cc=5739&ver=global|title=Melo abused by fans as Brazil return|date=4 July 2010|work=ESPN Soccernet|access-date=3 January 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021200825/http://soccernet.espn.go.com/world-cup/story/_/id/805973/ce/uk/?cc=5739&ver=global|archive-date=21 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nA quick, strong, tenacious, yet talented [[midfielder]], Melo is known in particular for his hard-working, energetic, physical, and hard-tackling playing style, which has earned him the nicknames ''Pitbull'' and ''Gladiator'', while in 2015 his Inter manager at the time, [[Roberto Mancini]], described Melo and his teammate [[Gary Medel]] as ''warriors''.<ref name=\"bullish\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzettaworld.com/features/inter-title-challenge-melo-medel/?refresh_ce-cp|title=Inter's title hopes spurred by bullish Melo and Medel|last=|first=|date=21 September 2015|work=La Gazzetta dello Sport|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809160951/http://www.gazzettaworld.com/features/inter-title-challenge-melo-medel/?refresh_ce-cp|archive-date=9 August 2016|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=time>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/live-scores/news/y=2012/m=1/news=felipe-melo-time-will-come-again-1567389.html|title=Felipe Melo: My time will come again|publisher=FIFA|date=12 January 2012|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=corsa>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/it/news/2/serie-a/2015/09/21/15576002/medel-e-melo-simboli-della-nuova-inter-tanta-corsa-e|title=Medel e Melo simboli della nuova Inter: tanta corsa e sacrificio al servizio della squadra|work=Goal.com|language=Italian|date=21 September 2015|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref> He is able to play as a [[Central midfielder|central]] or [[box-to-box midfielder]], but is usually deployed as a [[defensive midfielder]], where his stamina, power, tactical intelligence, and ball-winning abilities aid him in breaking down opposing plays, while his good all-round skills, first touch, and passing allow him subsequently to distribute the ball to his more offensive-minded teammates.<ref name=time/><ref name=corsa/><ref name=\"A Sure Thing? Not in This World Cup\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/07/03/sports/soccer/03iht-wcrob.html?_r=0|title=A Sure Thing? Not in This World Cup|work=The New York Times|author1=Rob Hughes|date=2 July 2010|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzettaworld.com/news/serie-a/inter/felipe-melo-dirty-work/?refresh_ce-cp|title=Felipe Melo happy to do Inter dirty work|work=La Gazzetta dello Sport|author1=Paul Sumeet|date=27 September 2015|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/news/inter-rispunta-felipe-melo-496648|title=Inter: Mancini richiama Felipe Melo|work=Calciomercato.com|language=Italian|date=29 June 2015|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/news/icardi-no-e-l-inter-di-melo-e-medel-913558|title=Icardi? No, \u00e8 l'Inter di Melo e Medel|work=calciomercato.com|language=Italian|date=21 September 2015|accessdate=19 January 2017}}</ref> In addition to his defensive attributes, he is also known for his dynamism and ability to make late runs into the area from midfield, which occasionally enables him to provide an additional attacking outlet to his teams.<ref name=time/> Throughout his career, Melo has stood out for his leadership on the pitch, although he has also equally been criticised for his aggression and tendency to pick up cards.<ref name=\"bullish\"/><ref name=\"A Sure Thing? Not in This World Cup\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/internazionale/story/2595963/felipe-melo-accepts-he-is-a-nasty-player|title=Inter Milan midfielder Felipe Melo accepts he is a 'nasty player'|work=ESPN FC|author1=Ben Gladwell|date=4 September 2015|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nMelo is married to Roberta<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/selecao-brasileira/noticia/2010/05/no-ritmo-do-assobio-da-familia-felipe-melo-se-garante-na-selecao.html No ritmo do assobio da fam\u00edlia, Felipe Melo se garante na sele\u00e7\u00e3o]. Globoesporte.globo.com. Retrieved on 31 May 2012.</ref> and they have one daughter (Pietra) and three sons, Davi, Linyker (who he named after the [[England national football team|English]] centre forward [[Gary Lineker]]),<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/sep/09/the-knowledge-footballers-named-after-footballers], The Guardian online, 9 September 2015</ref> and Bernardo.\n\nOn 18 June 2013, through [[Twitter]] and [[Facebook]], Melo offended Renato Maur\u00edcio Prado, a pundit of [[Fox Sports]] channel. Among another names callings, Melo called Prado \"coward\", \"arsehole\" and \"the most famous cuckold of sporting journalism\".<ref>[http://placar.abril.com.br/materia/felipe-melo-critica-renato-mauricio-prado-em-seu-facebook]{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://esportes.terra.com.br/flamengo/felipe-melo-desabafa-contra-jornalista-corno-mais-famoso-da-imprensa,23ccdbb25885f310VgnVCM3000009acceb0aRCRD.html|title=Felipe Melo desabafa contra jornalista: \"corno mais famoso da imprensa\"|date=18 June 2013|work=Terra}}</ref> Prado sued Melo in August.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esportes.terra.com.br/futebol/chamado-de-corno-comentarista-entra-com-processo-contra-felipe-melo,8764d40cea470410VgnVCM4000009bcceb0aRCRD.html|title=Chamado de \"corno\", comentarista entra com processo contra Felipe Melo|date=12 August 2013|work=Terra}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 June 2014, Melo was on vacation with his family and friend in [[Las Vegas]]. Whilst enjoying dinner with his family and friends, a former football player and his friend handed Melo a hand-written paper stating \"Sampiyon Fenerbah\u00e7e \u2013 which means Champion Fenerbah\u00e7e\". [[Fenerbah\u00e7e S.K. (football)|Fenerbah\u00e7e]], the main opponent of Galatasaray, had finished as Turkish S\u00fcper Lig champions for the 2013\u201314 season, which had just concluded. Melo responded to the note by showing the two his middle finger and by kicking one of them. The case was taken to American police.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/spor/futbol/26544606.asp|title=Melo'nun Las Vegas'ta '\u015fampiyon Fener' kavgas\u0131|author=Koray DURKAL|date=3 June 2014|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nMelo endorsed [[Jair Bolsonaro]] in the [[Brazilian general election, 2018|2018 Brazilian presidential election]].<ref>[https://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2017/05/01/felipe-melo-declara-apoio-a-jair-bolsonaro-em-2018.htm Felipe Melo declara apoio a Bolsonaro em 2018 e critica \"vagabundos\"]</ref><ref>[http://www.foxsports.com.br/news/302592-felipe-melo-faz-video-parabenizando-os-trabalhadores-brasileiros-e-diz-bolsonaro-neles Felipe Melo faz v\u00eddeo parabenizando os trabalhadores brasileiros e diz: \"Bolsonaro neles\"]</ref> He dedicated his winning goal against [[Chapecoense]] in October 2019 to the president, a fan of Palmeiras.<ref>{{cite news |title=Felipe Melo faz homenagem a Jair Bolsonaro ap\u00f3s gol da vit\u00f3ria|trans-title=Felipe Melo makes homage to Jair Bolsonaro after winning goal |url=https://www.lance.com.br/fora-de-campo/felipe-melo-faz-homenagem-jair-bolsonaro-apos-gol-vitoria.html |accessdate=7 November 2019 |work=Lance! |date=17 October 2019 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|29 January 2018}}.<ref>{{NFT player|id=29935|name=Melo, Felipe| accessdate = 9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageID=30&kisiID=1432017|title=FELIPE MELO DE CARVALHO| date = 9 April 2012|work=Turkish Football Federation| accessdate = 9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mackolik.com/Futbolcu/22730/Felipe-Melo|title=Felipe Melo de Carvalho| date = 9 April 2012|work=Mackolik.com| accessdate = 9 April 2012}}</ref><ref>Soccerway, Accessed on 29 January 2018</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental \n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]]\n|[[2001 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|2001]]\n|3||1||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| || || ||3||1\n|-\n|[[2002 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|2002]]\n|21||2||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| || || ||21||2\n|-\n|[[2003 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|2003]]\n|2||0||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| || || ||2||0\n|-\n!Total\n!26!!3!!colspan=\"2\"| !!colspan=\"2\"| !!colspan=\"2\"| !! !! !!26!!3\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]]\n|[[2003 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|2003]]\n|31||2||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| || || ||31||2\n|-\n!Total\n!31!!2!!colspan=\"2\"| !!colspan=\"2\"| !!colspan=\"2\"| !! !! !!31!!2\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Gr\u00eamio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|Gr\u00eamio]]\n|[[2004 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|2004]]\n|19||3||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| ||colspan=\"2\"| || || ||19||3\n|-\n!Total\n!19!!3!!colspan=\"2\"| !!colspan=\"2\"| !!colspan=\"2