dtimbers.com/news/2007/05/timbers-introduce-new-owner-merritt-paulson|archivedate=November 27, 2010}}</ref> ||rowspan=\"3\" | [[Merritt Paulson]] || 2007&ndash;2009\n|-\n| 2010 || [[USSF Division 2 Professional League|D-2 Pro League]]\n|-\n| Peregrine Sports LLC<ref>{{cite web|title=City completes deal to bring MLS to Portland|url=http://www.portlandtimbers.com/news/2010/01/city-completes-deal-to-bring-mls-to-portland|publisher=Portland Timbers|accessdate=June 27, 2011|date=January 21, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101127204405/http://portlandtimbers.com/news/2010/01/city-completes-deal-to-bring-mls-to-portland|archive-date=November 27, 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref> || 2011&ndash; || [[Major League Soccer|MLS]]\n|}\n\n=== Managerial History ===\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:left; margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:#EAE827\" width=130px |<span style=\"color:#004812;\">Name</span>\n!style=\"background:#EAE827\" width=40px |<span style=\"color:#004812;\">Nat.</span>\n!style=\"background:#EAE827\" width=100px |<span style=\"color:#004812;\">Years</span>\n!style=\"background:#EAE827\" width=100px |<span style=\"color:#004812;\">League</span>\n|-\n| [[Vic Crowe]] || {{flagicon|WAL}} || 1975&ndash;1976 ||rowspan=\"5\" | [[North American Soccer League|NASL]]\n|-\n| [[Brian Tiler]] || {{flagicon|ENG}} || 1977\n|-\n| [[Don Megson]] || {{flagicon|ENG}} || 1978&ndash;1980\n|-\n| [[Peter Warner]] || {{flagicon|ENG}} || 1980 (interim)\n|-\n| [[Vic Crowe]] || {{flagicon|WAL}} || 1980&ndash;1982\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | [[Bernie Fagan]] ||rowspan=\"2\" | {{flagicon|ENG}} || 1985 || [[Western Soccer Alliance|WACS]]\n|-\n| 1986&ndash;1988 || [[Western Soccer Alliance|WSA]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | [[John Bain (soccer)|John Bain]] ||rowspan=\"2\" | {{flagicon|SCO}} || 1989 || [[Western Soccer Alliance|WSL]]\n|-\n| 1990 || [[American Professional Soccer League|APSL]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | [[Bobby Howe (footballer born 1945)|Bobby Howe]] ||rowspan=\"2\" | {{flagicon|ENG}} || 2001&ndash;2004 || [[A-League (1995\u20132004)|A-League]]\n|-\n| 2005 ||rowspan=\"3\" | [[USL First Division|USL-1]]\n|-\n| [[Chris Agnello]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || 2006\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | [[Gavin Wilkinson]] ||rowspan=\"2\" | {{flagicon|NZL}} || 2007&ndash;2009\n|-\n| 2010 || [[USSF Division 2 Professional League|D-2 Pro League]]\n|-\n| [[John Spencer (Scottish footballer)|John Spencer]] || {{flagicon|SCO}} || 2011&ndash;2012 ||rowspan=\"3\"| [[Major League Soccer|MLS]]\n|-\n| [[Gavin Wilkinson]] || {{flagicon|NZL}} || 2012 (interim)\n|-\n| [[Caleb Porter]] || {{flagicon|USA}} || 2013\u20132017 \n|}\n\n==Notes==\n:A.&nbsp;{{note label|Alizadeh|A|^}} It was announced on March 30, 2005 that Portland Baseball Investment Group, headed by Abe Alizadeh, had agreed to buy the Timbers and the Portland Beavers baseball club from the Pacific Coast League.<ref>{{cite web|title=New Owners for Timbers|url=http://www.uslsoccer.com/home/95395.html|accessdate=June 30, 2011|publisher=United Soccer Leagues|date=March 30, 2005|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121013043948/http://www.uslsoccer.com/home/95395.html|archivedate=October 13, 2012}}</ref> The Timbers referred to Alizadeh as the Majority Owner in press releases throughout the 2005 and 2006 seasons. However, the sale was not officially completed until June 16, 2006.<ref name=\"pbig sale\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{Portland Timbers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:History Of Portland Timbers}}\n[[Category:Portland Timbers]]\n[[Category:History of soccer in the United States|Portland Timbers]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 10-10 \u2192 10\u201310 (3), 2-0 \u2192 2\u20130", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_the_Portland_Timbers_franchise"}
